# ⚙️ Feature Engineering

The following transformations were performed before model training:

| Feature             | Description                                        |
| ------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Label Encoding      | Encoded `Region`, `Model`, and `Source_Type`       |
| Deliveries_Lag1     | Previous delivery value used as a temporal feature |
| Rolling_Mean_3      | Three-period moving average of deliveries          |
| Chronological Split | 80% Training • 20% Testing (Time-aware split)      |

---

# 🤖 Machine Learning Models

| Model                   | Purpose                                       |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Linear Regression       | Baseline regression model                     |
| Random Forest Regressor | Ensemble model with hyperparameter tuning     |
| ARIMA                   | Time-series forecasting for future deliveries |

---

# 📈 Model Optimization

Random Forest was optimized using **GridSearchCV** with multiple combinations of:

* Number of Estimators
* Maximum Tree Depth
* Cross Validation

The optimized model was further analyzed using **Feature Importance**, highlighting the variables contributing most to delivery prediction.

---

# 📉 Time Series Analysis

To understand delivery trends over time, the project includes:

* Augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) Stationarity Test
* Time Series Validation
* ARIMA Model
* 12-Month Delivery Forecast
* Forecast Visualization

---

# 📋 Model Evaluation

The predictive models were evaluated using standard regression metrics:

| Metric                      | Description                              |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| **MAE**                     | Mean Absolute Error                      |
| **RMSE**                    | Root Mean Squared Error                  |
| **R² Score**                | Coefficient of Determination             |
| **5-Fold Cross Validation** | Model generalization performance         |
| **Feature Importance**      | Identification of influential predictors |

